Basic system utilities for Alchemy.

cat <file>
  Print file on the output. If file is not specified then
  standard input is used.

cp <source> <destination>
  Copy contents of one file to another.

date
  Print current date and time on the output.

echo <messages>...
  Print given messages on the output.

env <key>=<value>... <command> <arguments>
  Run program in a changed environment.

ls <directory>
  Print names of all files contained in given directory. If argument is
  not specified then list contents of the current working directory.

mkdir <directory>
  Make new empty directory in the file system.

mv <source> <destination>
  Move/rename file.

rm <files>...
  Remove specified files.
